Basically you need to tell the browser which Font Awesome family you want to use. Just like if you wanted `Arial` vs `Times` to display text on your site.

In your code block you should say:

    .icon:before {
      font-family: &quot;Font Awesome 5 Free&quot;;
      font-weight: 900;
      content: &quot;\f007&quot;;
    }

In the case of Font Awesome, it&#39;s a combination of `font-family` and `font-weight` that produce the different looks.

---
The real issue is that you&#39;re using the *free* version of FA which only includes the &quot;solid&quot; and &quot;Brands&quot; styles by specifying the 900 weight and the 400 weight. The features you&#39;re requesting are part of the Pro version.

[![enter image description here][1]][1]

Here&#39;s [FA&#39;s Documentation][2] on this issue.


