Try:
```
var constraints = {
  video: {
    width: {exact: 640},
    height: {exact: 480},
    frameRate: {
      ideal: 10,
      max: 15
    }
  }
};
```
Note though not all browsers on all platforms downscale to arbitrary dimensions, leaving you picking among discrete native modes instead. Seeing resolution changes is usually a sign of this, because of how [fitness distance](https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/getusermedia.html#dfn-fitness-distance) is calculated. So be prepared with a fallback if this fails. 

A better strategy may be to obtain the camera in the resolution you want first,  then use `applyConstraints` to reduce its framerate:
```
await stream.getVideoTracks()[0].applyConstraints({
  width: {exact: 640},
  height: {exact: 480},
  frameRate: {ideal: 10, max: 15}
]);
```
That way if it fails you still have a steam.

